{"word":"στρατία","slug":"στρατία","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>στρατία</b></el> <el>(στρᾰτία, <el>ionic</el> <el>-ιή, ἡ</el>,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>= <a href='S:στρατός'><el>στρατός</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>an army</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>: <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>a land force</i>, as distinguished from a fleet, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>generally, <i>a host, company, band</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>= <a href='S:στρατεία'><el>στρατεία</el></a>, <i>an expedition</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}